        <description>Install 1  $ sudo pacman -S docker # Community Repo   optional dependencies : 1 2  $ # btrfs-progs: btrfs backend support $ # pigz: parallel gzip compressor support   start and enable docker.service : 1  $ sudo systemctl enable --now docker.service   verify operation (note we have to run the command with sudo) : 1  $ sudo docker info   Configuration add dushaouai to the docker user group : 1  $ sudo gpasswd -a dushaouai docker   thus dushaouai is able to run the docker CLI command as a non-root user after reboot</description>
        
